LivingTrust Mortgage Bank has appointed Dr Olumide Adedeji as an executive director, effective January 1, 2022. The bank said in a statement that Adedeji would serve as executive director in charge of customer experience and business development. According to the statement, the appointment is subject to regulatory approval. It said before his appointment, Adedeji was the managing director of BWC Group, a holding company with subsidiaries in the hospitality, lottery, and real estate sectors. It said he also served as executive director of AICTP West Africa and group head of SME at Globacom Nigeria. According to the statement, Adedeji has over 11 years of experience in the banking sector in Nigeria and other African countries. It said until 2011, when he joined Globacom Nigeria, he was a deputy general manager and group head, retail and commercial banking of Sterling Bank Plc. “Before that, he worked at FCMB Plc, Standard Chartered Bank, Access Bank Plc, and Fidelity Bank Plc. He also had robust consultancy experience with Deloitte & Touche,” the bank said. It said Adedeji graduated with a Bachelor’s Degree in Physics from the University of Ibadan and later obtained both Masters and doctorate degrees from the same institution. “He is a fellow of the Institute of Chartered Accountants of Nigeria. He is also an associate of the Chartered Institute of Taxation of Nigeria, Institute of Credit Administration, Nigerian Institute of Management, and Certified Forensic Investigation Professionals,” the statement added. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com